45
00:04:11,173 --> 00:04:13,103
主演:克丽斯汀・克鲁克

46
00:04:12,773 --> 00:04:17,673
谁来拯救我

47
00:04:15,763 --> 00:04:17,773
主演:迈克尔・罗森巴姆

48
00:04:19,273 --> 00:04:22,913
我不在乎你是怎么做到

49
00:04:19,373 --> 00:04:21,503
主演：埃里克・约翰森

50
00:04:23,103 --> 00:04:27,013
只要你留下，和我在一起

51
00:04:26,473 --> 00:04:28,573
主演：山姆・琼斯三世

52
00:04:27,413 --> 00:04:33,713
快来吧，我一直在等待着你

53
00:04:30,473 --> 00:04:33,112
主演：艾利森・麦克

54
00:04:34,493 --> 00:04:37,212
主演：安妮特・奥图尔

55
00:04:39,472 --> 00:04:42,163
约翰・施耐得 饰演 强纳森・肯特

56
00:04:39,612 --> 00:04:43,912
我一直留着整个世界只为你闪耀

57
00:04:43,812 --> 00:04:46,812
超人始创作者:杰瑞・希杰尔和乔・夏斯特

58
00:04:44,112 --> 00:04:47,412
留下，留下

59
00:04:48,412 --> 00:04:50,412
快出现吧

60
00:04:48,612 --> 00:04:51,202
电视策划:阿尔弗雷德・哥夫，麦尔斯・米莱

61
00:04:53,545 --> 00:04:56,745
第十四集:零后果

62
00:04:53,545 --> 00:04:56,745
一周以前{\r}

63
00:04:57,578 --> 00:05:00,274
没有什么比奥斯丁先生50分钟 的英语课…
There is nothing like 50 minutes of Mr. Austin's English class...

64
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:00,400
客串主演:柯林・纳麦克

65
00:05:00,447 --> 00:05:03,439
- …更能激发食欲了 - 没有什么比周一要交的6页学生传记…
-...that works up an appetite. -Nothing like a student biography...

66
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,000
卡梅隆・戴伊
-...due Monday to help me lose mine. -The biography part...

67
00:05:03,617 --> 00:05:05,949
- …更能败掉我的食欲了 - 是因为传记那部分…

68
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:08,918
…还是因为我们被胡乱分配了啊
...or the fact that our student subjects were randomly assigned?

69
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:09,000
埃里克・布瑞克

70
00:05:09,089 --> 00:05:11,353
皮特听信说，抽签配对的事被暗中操作过
Pete's convinced that the drawing was fixed.

71
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:13,500
联合执行制片:格列哥・比曼
There are a dozen ladies in our class, each worthy of lengthy interrogation.

72
00:05:11,525 --> 00:05:15,222
我们班上有那么多女生 个个都值得搞一番详细的调查

73
00:05:15,396 --> 00:05:19,298
- 我偏得和斯坦・吉布森配成一组，调查他吗？ - 那个学生便利店的经理？
-I get stuck with Stan Gibson? -The manager of the student store?

74
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:18,500
监督制片:马克・伏黑顿

75
00:05:19,466 --> 00:05:20,933
- 我听说他非常… - 高效？
-I hear he's very-- -Efficient?

76
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:22,500
制片:迈克尔・格林
Very funny. I'm about to learn more about the art of selling "Go Crow" pennants...

77
00:05:21,101 --> 00:05:24,730
搞笑，我正要学习乌鸦队旗的销售艺术…

78
00:05:24,905 --> 00:05:27,135
…简直不是人受的
...than any human should have to endure.

79
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:27,300
制片:道里斯・伊根

80
00:05:27,307 --> 00:05:30,140
从下课到现在你一直在笑 谁成了你的受害者了？
You haven't stopped smiling since we left. Who's your victim?

81
00:05:30,310 --> 00:05:33,473
正是杰出的肯特先生
The illustrious Mr. Kent himself.

82
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:35,300
联合制片:格雷格・沃克
-Me? -I take it back.

83
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:34,942
- 我？ - 我收回你迫害人家的说法
Chloe's the one with the challenge.

84
00:05:35,115 --> 00:05:36,912
克罗伊，你真是个勇于挑战的人

85
00:05:37,084 --> 00:05:38,551
- 什么？ - 我没恶意，克拉克…
-Excuse me? -No offense, Clark...

86
00:05:38,719 --> 00:05:40,744
…不过要想从你身上找出六页有趣的事
...but digging up six pages of interesting on you...

87
00:05:40,921 --> 00:05:43,389
- …得做点严重的发掘工作了 - 我也做过不少事的啊
-...is gonna require serious excavation. -I do stuff.

88
00:05:43,300 --> 00:05:45,300
制片:鲍勃・哈格罗夫
Yes, and I'm sure that once I deploy my journalistic skills on you...

89
00:05:43,557 --> 00:05:46,685
对，只要充分利用了我的新闻调查能力…

90
00:05:46,860 --> 00:05:48,452
…肯定能发掘出你的料的
...l'll unearth a skeleton or two.

91
00:05:48,629 --> 00:05:52,065
克洛伊，这是一个班级作业 不是腐败丑闻调查
You know, Chloe, this is a class project, not a corruption scandal.

92
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:52,000
联合执行制片:肯・霍顿

93
00:05:52,232 --> 00:05:54,666
别紧张，你本来也没什么要隐瞒吧？
Relax. It's not like you have anything to hide, right?

94
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:55,500
剧本:马克・伏黑顿
Come on, Clark, cough up. Who'd you get?

95
00:05:54,835 --> 00:05:57,531
克拉克，老实交代，你抽到谁要调查？

96
00:05:57,704 --> 00:06:00,036
不会是拉娜・郎吧
Don't tell me. Lana Lang.

97
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,300
故事:阿尔弗雷德・哥夫，麦尔斯・米莱

98
00:06:00,207 --> 00:06:02,437
瞧他那表情，不用看纸条都知道
Just look at his face, you don't even have to see it.

99
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,300
导演:迈克尔・卡特曼
Like I said, definitely rigged.

100
00:06:02,609 --> 00:06:04,668
正如我所说，肯定有暗中操纵

101
00:06:04,845 --> 00:06:07,643
- 我猜你会赶快动笔了？ - 我能搞好这作业的
-I assume you'll start your paper ASAP? -It's all gonna work out.

102
00:06:07,815 --> 00:06:10,579
我在帮拉娜准备塔龙开张
I'm helping Lana at the Talon getting ready for the opening.

103
00:06:10,751 --> 00:06:14,346
惠特尼忙于他父亲的商店 代理男友当然要顶上了
Surrogate boyfriend does the heavy lifting while Whitney works at his dad's store.

104
00:06:14,521 --> 00:06:15,954
- 说到这个… - 等等
-On that note.... -Wait.

105
00:06:16,123 --> 00:06:18,148
你打算什么时候接受我采访
When are you gonna sit down to do my interview?

106
00:06:18,325 --> 00:06:21,692
好吧，随时
Right. I'll be around.

107
00:06:21,929 --> 00:06:24,022
他在敷衍我吗？
Did he just blow me off?

108
00:06:24,198 --> 00:06:27,895
你进一步，他退两步，别理他了
One step forward, two steps back. Come on.

109
00:06:32,673 --> 00:06:34,698
你答应过一切会按时准备好
You promised everything would be ready on time.

110
00:06:34,875 --> 00:06:37,275
可那时水管还没裂
That was before the plumbing started leaking.

111
00:06:37,444 --> 00:06:40,845
- 太长时间没更换了 - 得花多长时间修理？
-Hasn't been replaced in years. -How long will that take?

112
00:06:41,014 --> 00:06:46,782
不上去检查，没法给你准确答案
I can't really give you a straight answer, not until I crawl up there.

113
00:06:47,321 --> 00:06:50,586
翻新老店，老毛病当然不可避免
You resurrect the past, you get the problems that come with it.

114
00:06:50,757 --> 00:06:53,555
莱克斯・卢瑟马上过来，他需要具体数字…
Lex Luthor's going to be by later. He's going to need numbers...

115
00:06:53,727 --> 00:06:57,390
…施工安排和一个更好的解释
...and a timetable and a better explanation than that.

116
00:07:04,638 --> 00:07:09,439
- 抱歉，我们还没开张 - 我来申请经理助理的职位
-Sorry, we're not open yet. -It's about the assistant manager position.

117
00:07:09,610 --> 00:07:11,942
我来晚了，如果还能领张申请表…
I know I'm late, but if I can get an application....

118
00:07:12,112 --> 00:07:16,811
- 嗯，好，稍等 - 非常感谢，怎么称呼?
-Yeah, yeah, just give me a second. -Great. Really appreciate this, Miss...?

119
00:07:16,984 --> 00:07:18,212
- 郎 - 郎小姐
-Lang. -Lang.

120
00:07:18,385 --> 00:07:21,946
不过，我姨妈要到下周才能给你面试
And just to warn you, my aunt's not taking any more interviews until next week.

121
00:07:22,122 --> 00:07:25,421
没关系，我有的是时间
Well, that's all right. I happen to have all the time in the world.

122
00:07:25,592 --> 00:07:28,755
- 我叫裘德・罗伊斯 - 你好
-I'm Jude Royce. -Hi.

123
00:07:29,396 --> 00:07:32,957
我听说莱克斯・卢瑟在这个项目中有股份
So I understand that Lex Luthor has a stake in this project.

124
00:07:34,034 --> 00:07:36,298
他是业主之一，怎么？你认识他？
Yeah, he's one of the owners. Why? Do you know him?

125
00:07:37,604 --> 00:07:41,165
- 很久以前在大都市的时候 - 一定很有趣
-A lifetime ago in Metropolis. -Must have been interesting.

126
00:07:41,708 --> 00:07:45,144
其实他来斯摩维尔是有原因的
Well, let's just say there's a reason he's in Smallville.

127
00:07:46,513 --> 00:07:49,846
想听我的建议吗？离他远点
You know my advice? Stay away from him.

128
00:07:50,284 --> 00:07:53,776
只要莱克斯插手，事情就会变糟
When Lex gets involved, things usually turn out badly.

129
00:08:12,839 --> 00:08:14,966
你来这干什么？我们之前说好的
What are you doing here? We had an understanding.

130
00:08:15,142 --> 00:08:17,406
那晚之后，我们再也不联系
After that night, we were never to have any contact.

131
00:08:17,578 --> 00:08:19,705
- 我看到他了，莱克斯 - 谁？
-I saw him, Lex. -Who?

132
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:21,643
裘德
Jude.

133
00:08:22,482 --> 00:08:25,542
- 我们都知道那是不可能的 - 听我说！他还活着
-We both know that's impossible. -Listen to me! He's alive.

134
00:08:25,719 --> 00:08:27,380
我到哪都能看到他
Everywhere I go, I see him.

135
00:08:27,554 --> 00:08:30,114
- 他在跟踪我 - 冷静点，凯瑟
-He's stalking me. -Kasich. Calm down.

136
00:08:30,924 --> 00:08:32,323
我没疯
I'm not crazy.

137
00:08:33,193 --> 00:08:37,527
- 这个人说他要什么了吗？ - 说了，要真相
-This man say what he wanted? -Yeah. The truth.

138
00:08:41,101 --> 00:08:43,228
听着，我在城里有一间公寓
Listen. I keep an apartment in the city.

139
00:08:43,403 --> 00:08:47,931
那很安全，你呆在那，等我电话
It's very secure. You stay there and wait for my call.

140
00:08:56,617 --> 00:08:58,608
- 嘿，莱克斯 - 你好
-Hey, Lex. -Hey.

141
00:08:58,785 --> 00:09:01,447
- 那是谁? - 闲人吧
-Who was that? -Nobody.

142
00:09:05,058 --> 00:09:06,423
听说咱这边漏水了
I hear we sprung a leak.

143
00:09:09,529 --> 00:09:10,826
事情都还顺利吗?
Is everything all right?

144
00:09:11,898 --> 00:09:14,594
- 有点不顺 - 别紧张，漏水而已
-Just a little weirded out. -Relax, it's just a leak.

145
00:09:14,835 --> 00:09:18,066
不是，你一个朋友过来，申请助理的工作
No, a friend of yours came by, applied for the assistant manager position.

146
00:09:18,505 --> 00:09:21,838
他让我离你远点
He told me to stay away from you.

147
00:09:24,311 --> 00:09:26,541
他叫什么
What was his name?

148
00:09:30,617 --> 00:09:31,879
裘德・罗伊斯
Jude Royce.

149
00:09:41,395 --> 00:09:44,421
- 怎么了，莱克斯？ - 他什么时候离开的?
-What is it, Lex? -When did he leave?

150
00:09:44,598 --> 00:09:46,031
就在你进来之前
Just before you came in.

151
00:09:58,945 --> 00:10:02,540
莱克斯，裘德・罗伊斯是谁？
Lex, who's Jude Royce?

152
00:10:02,783 --> 00:10:05,684
相信我，克拉克 虽然我不知道拉娜今天见到的是谁
Trust me, Clark, I have no idea who Lana met today...

153
00:10:05,852 --> 00:10:08,082
但不可能是他
...but it couldn't have been him.

154
00:10:10,624 --> 00:10:13,286
别担心这个，克拉克，我不担心
Don't worry about it, Clark. I'm not.

155
00:10:28,075 --> 00:10:29,940
怎么了？
What's going on?

156
00:10:30,677 --> 00:10:31,803
我不知道
I don't know!

157
00:10:40,620 --> 00:10:43,111
摸摸仪表盘下面
Feel under the dash.

158
00:10:54,134 --> 00:10:57,103
看来有人趁我们进去时搞了点创意啊
Looks like someone decided to get creative while I was inside.

159
00:10:57,704 --> 00:10:59,035
那尖叫声是怎么回事？
What were the screams?

160
00:10:59,573 --> 00:11:02,872
我猜是有人变态的恶作剧
I assume it's someone's twisted idea of a joke.

161
00:11:03,043 --> 00:11:05,807
很成功啊，招来了一堆人
And a successful one. We've managed to draw a crowd.

162
00:11:11,685 --> 00:11:16,054
- 莱克斯 - 克拉克，你真不用担心这事
-Lex. -Clark, this really doesn't concern you.

163
00:11:28,034 --> 00:11:29,865
有人在家吗？
Hello, anybody home?

164
00:11:30,070 --> 00:11:33,471
嘿，我们在做录音访问，儿子
Hey, pull up a microphone, son.

165
00:11:35,008 --> 00:11:37,499
- 克罗伊，怎么了？ - 因为我找不到你…
-Chloe, what's going on? -Since I couldn't find you...

166
00:11:37,677 --> 00:11:40,510
…就决定从故事源头开始我的传记调查
...I decided to start my biographical inquiry at the beginning.

167
00:11:40,680 --> 00:11:42,648
不像我某个所谓的朋友…
Unlike a certain so-called friend of mine...

168
00:11:42,816 --> 00:11:45,011
…你父母很通情达理地接受了我的采访
...your parents gracefully agreed to be interviewed.

169
00:11:45,185 --> 00:11:48,245
克洛伊问了我们一些有趣的问题，克拉克
Chloe's been asking us some very interesting questions, Clark.

170
00:11:48,722 --> 00:11:51,555
谢谢，还有几个问题要探讨，所以…
Thank you. Now, we just have a few more to go, so....

171
00:11:52,292 --> 00:11:54,226
聊聊以前的事吧
We were talking about the early days.

172
00:11:54,427 --> 00:11:56,657
你们是怎么领养克拉克的？
Now, what was involved in adopting Clark?

173
00:11:57,998 --> 00:12:01,798
只是次很普通的领养
Well, it was-- It was just like any normal adoption, I guess.

174
00:12:01,968 --> 00:12:05,267
你能告诉我这个过程吗？ 这个过程花费了几个礼拜还是几个月？
Can you take me through the process? Did it takes weeks or months?

175
00:12:05,438 --> 00:12:08,532
你们用了律师，还是通过代理人…?
Did you guys use a lawyer, or did you go through an agen--?

176
00:12:08,708 --> 00:12:13,611
该死，录音带用完了 没关系，我车上还有几盘
Shoot. I'm out of tape. That's okay, I've got some extra C-90s in my car.

177
00:12:13,780 --> 00:12:15,543
我很快回来
I'll be right back.

178
00:12:18,752 --> 00:12:21,016
克洛伊为了学校作业，在调查你的生活吗？
Chloe's researching your life for a school project?

179
00:12:21,188 --> 00:12:23,656
- 什么时候的事？ - 我们今天分的作业
-When did that happen? -We just got the assignment today.

180
00:12:23,824 --> 00:12:25,553
没想到她真会像迈克・华莱士一样较真
I didn't know she was gonna go Mike Wallace.

181
00:12:25,759 --> 00:12:27,386
儿子，我们不介意谈论你…
We don't mind talking about you...

182
00:12:27,561 --> 00:12:30,121
…可她要是再问关于领养的事…
...but if she starts asking questions about the adoption....

183
00:12:30,530 --> 00:12:32,794
领养怎么了？
What about the adoption?

184
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,558
有什么我应该知道的事？
Is there something I should know?

185
00:12:37,404 --> 00:12:39,497
当然，我们需要编个故事…
Well, of course, we had to make up a story...

186
00:12:39,673 --> 00:12:41,538
…但这更复杂
...but it's more complicated than that.

187
00:12:41,708 --> 00:12:44,700
就说我们不想任何人调查这方面好了
Let's just say it's a subject we would rather not have anyone explore.

188
00:12:44,878 --> 00:12:46,277
不好意思，打扰到你们了吗？
Sorry. Am I interrupting?

189
00:12:46,980 --> 00:12:49,505
克拉克，既然你终于走进我的调查圈子…
Clark, now that you're finally spinning in my orbit...

190
00:12:49,683 --> 00:12:52,049
…我也有些事想问你
...I have a couple of pertinents for you too.

191
00:12:52,219 --> 00:12:54,244
实际上，我只是过来看一下
Actually, this is just a pit stop for me.

192
00:12:54,421 --> 00:12:56,651
我正要去找拉娜准备我的论文
I'm on my way to meet Lana to work on my paper.

193
00:12:57,324 --> 00:13:02,261
克拉克，不是我有意瞎猜，但你是在回避我吗？
You know, Clark, not to strike a paranoid note, but are you avoiding me?

194
00:13:06,333 --> 00:13:08,062
明天，我保证
Tomorrow, I promise.

195
00:13:13,073 --> 00:13:15,439
好的，这不是一个正式问题…
Okay, this isn't an official question...

196
00:13:15,609 --> 00:13:18,237
…我也不想你们误会我这问题…
...and I don't want you guys to take it the wrong way...

197
00:13:18,411 --> 00:13:21,312
…不过，你们的儿子一直这么奇怪吗？
...but has your son always been this strange?

198
00:13:24,885 --> 00:13:27,080
- 感觉怎么样？ - 什么感觉？
-How does it feel? -Feel?

199
00:13:27,254 --> 00:13:30,951
单枪匹马就把差点变成停车场的塔龙救回来？
To single-handedly bring the Talon back from the brink of becoming a parking garage?

200
00:13:32,792 --> 00:13:36,125
这种被依靠，肩负责任的感觉很好
It's nice, you know, being counted on, having responsibility.

201
00:13:36,296 --> 00:13:39,163
- 人们对我也会不一样了 - 这下不会觉得你是脆弱的人了
-People treat you differently. -Like you won't break.

202
00:13:39,699 --> 00:13:43,328
终于感觉自己慢慢脱下了公主的外衣
Finally feel like I'm shedding that fairy-princess costume.

203
00:13:55,382 --> 00:13:58,283
- 莱克斯，你来干嘛? - 承包商打电话给我
-Lex, what are you doing here? -Contractor called.

204
00:13:58,451 --> 00:14:01,284
说他有了估价，希望我来这找他
Said he had an estimate, wanted me to meet him here.

205
00:14:11,197 --> 00:14:13,062
怎么了？
What the hell?

206
00:14:13,466 --> 00:14:15,457
你还好吗？
Are you okay?

207
00:14:16,536 --> 00:14:21,439
我从后门进来时，有人扑过来…
Yeah. I came in the back door and some guy jumped me...

208
00:14:21,641 --> 00:14:24,337
…逼我给他开门，还打了我的头
...and forced me to let him in and bashed me over the head.

209
00:14:24,511 --> 00:14:26,502
你看见他的脸没?
Did you see his face?

210
00:14:27,213 --> 00:14:28,840
没有
No.

211
00:14:30,917 --> 00:14:32,043
看
Look.

212
00:14:35,555 --> 00:14:39,548
我锁门的时候它不在那，我去叫警察
That wasn't there when I locked up. I'll go call the police.

213
00:14:43,863 --> 00:14:46,058
莱克斯，上面有你的名字
Lex, your name's on it.

214
00:15:03,883 --> 00:15:06,249
写的是“零后果”
Zero consequences.

215
00:15:27,173 --> 00:15:29,368
你怎么样了？
How you holding up?

216
00:15:29,876 --> 00:15:33,073
本来还好…可一看到那手
I was fine...until it showed up.

217
00:15:33,246 --> 00:15:35,578
是的，问得真愚蠢
Yeah, stupid question.

218
00:15:35,749 --> 00:15:38,616
怎么会有这么变态的人做这种事？
What kind of a sick person would do a thing like that?

219
00:15:39,719 --> 00:15:41,186
我不知道
I don't know.

220
00:15:41,521 --> 00:15:43,989
从没见过莱克斯这么不安
But I've never seen Lex so freaked out before.

221
00:15:44,157 --> 00:15:46,091
我也没
Join the club.

222
00:15:46,826 --> 00:15:51,354
那人警告我，凡是莱克斯插手的事都没好下场
That guy warned me. He said everything Lex touches ends badly.

223
00:15:52,065 --> 00:15:54,192
关于他和他的过去，我们到底知道多少?
How much do we really know about him and his past?

224
00:15:55,935 --> 00:15:59,234
我希望你们知道我对此多么抱歉
I want you both to know how truly sorry I am about this.

225
00:15:59,406 --> 00:16:01,306
我保证不会影响开张
I promise this won't affect the grand opening.

226
00:16:02,142 --> 00:16:05,339
可我们会在开张前就已经声名狼藉了
We're going to be infamous before we even open the doors.

227
00:16:16,523 --> 00:16:19,515
你知道他是谁吗？盒子里那手的…
Do you know who he is? The guy in the.... You know.

228
00:16:19,692 --> 00:16:24,652
马克斯・凯瑟，多年前我们在大都会相识
Max Kasich. And yes, I knew him a long time ago in Metropolis.

229
00:16:25,932 --> 00:16:28,196
你知道谁可能对他做那种事吗？
Do you have any idea who might have done this to him?

230
00:16:28,368 --> 00:16:29,665
不知道
Not at all.

231
00:16:32,105 --> 00:16:34,767
会是你的老朋友裘德・罗伊斯吗？
What about your old friend Jude Royce?

232
00:16:35,375 --> 00:16:38,936
- 我相信不是他，克拉克 - 为什么？
-I doubt it could have been him, Clark. -Why?

233
00:16:39,512 --> 00:16:42,072
因为他已经死了三年了
Because he's been dead for three years.

234
00:16:49,355 --> 00:16:51,380
我从肯特家得到的唯一…
The only information I got from the Kents...

235
00:16:51,558 --> 00:16:54,220
…惊天动地的消息就是克拉克不喜欢豌豆
...was the earth-shattering admission that Clark hates peas.

236
00:16:54,394 --> 00:16:57,363
塔龙出现了断肢，但你所谈论的只有克拉克？
A body part shows up at the Talon and all you can talk about is Clark?

237
00:16:57,530 --> 00:17:00,556
你分不出轻重吗？莱克斯・卢瑟肯定与其有关
Where are your priorities? Lex Luthor must be mixed up in this.

238
00:17:00,733 --> 00:17:04,100
- 别这样，我知道你对卢瑟有意见 - 岂止是意见
-I know you've got issues with the Luthors-- -More than issues.

239
00:17:04,270 --> 00:17:05,931
你知道卢瑟家族是怎么对我家人的
You know what they did to my family.

240
00:17:06,106 --> 00:17:07,903
这些信息也要一条一条来谈
One piece of investigative information at a time.

241
00:17:08,074 --> 00:17:10,634
- 现在，关于克拉克… - 克洛伊，你想从我这里知道什么？
-Now, about Clark.... -Chloe, what do you want from me?

242
00:17:10,810 --> 00:17:13,278
如果把别人都比作高级矿泉水 克拉克也是像自来水一样普通
In a world of designer water, Clark's from the tap.

243
00:17:13,446 --> 00:17:17,143
我知道，但你认识他最长时间 我所要的不过是一点趣闻轶事罢了…
I know, but you've known him the longest. All I need is just a little anecdote...

244
00:17:17,317 --> 00:17:20,343
…只要一点关于他灰暗过去的消息
...just a small piece of information from Clark's deep, dark past.

245
00:17:20,520 --> 00:17:22,954
一年级时发生了件事
Well, there was something back in the first grade.

246
00:17:23,123 --> 00:17:25,990
谢谢！这可比我这两天得到的信息还要多
Thank you! That's more than I've uncovered the past two days.

247
00:17:26,159 --> 00:17:27,626
现在，拜托，快给我讲吧
Now, please, let's continue.

248
00:17:27,794 --> 00:17:29,455
当时有个大我们三级的小霸王
There was a bully three grades ahead.

249
00:17:29,629 --> 00:17:32,097
这家伙要把学校里每个人都揍一顿
This dude was determined to pound dents into every kid.

250
00:17:32,265 --> 00:17:35,200
那天轮到我倒霉，他正要揍我…
One day it was my turn. He was just about to take my head off...

251
00:17:35,368 --> 00:17:38,633
- …克拉克就跳到我们中间 - 克拉克竟然干涉打架
-...when Clark jumped between us. -So Clark ran interference?

252
00:17:40,206 --> 00:17:42,140
不过，这听起来没什么特别，皮特…
Now, as kind as that sounds, Pete...

253
00:17:42,308 --> 00:17:44,742
…我不认为它符合“惊人猛料”的标准
...I don't think it falls into the "something amazing" test.

254
00:17:44,911 --> 00:17:46,173
- 什么标准？ - 我还没说完
-What test? -I'm not finished.

255
00:17:46,346 --> 00:17:48,871
克拉克不只是推了他，连门都撞破了
Clark didn't just push Braindead, he put him through a door...

256
00:17:49,048 --> 00:17:52,415
…当时遍地碎片，合叶都断了 我至今不知道他是怎么做到的
...as in splinters and broken hinges. How he did it, I still have no idea.

257
00:17:52,585 --> 00:17:55,577
- 那家伙个头至少是我们两倍 - 克拉克 ，怎么解释？
-Guy was at least twice our size. -Clark, any comments?

258
00:17:58,024 --> 00:18:01,824
我们那时才六岁，两倍也只不过三英尺高
Well, we were, you know, 6 years old. Twice our size was three feet tall.

259
00:18:02,362 --> 00:18:04,489
如果想听更多以前的轶事 还是问本人吧
If you need more ancient history, ask the source.

260
00:18:04,664 --> 00:18:07,189
我在学生商店还约了人
I've got an appointment at the student store.

261
00:18:07,367 --> 00:18:09,130
祝你调查愉快
Have fun.

262
00:18:09,469 --> 00:18:12,905
如此，克拉克・肯特的秘密更神秘了
And so the mystery that isn't Clark Kent deepens.

263
00:18:13,072 --> 00:18:14,300
- 秘密？ - 对
-Mystery? -Yeah.

264
00:18:14,474 --> 00:18:16,442
因为你总是扮演着妨碍者的角色…
Since you continue to play obstructionist...

265
00:18:16,609 --> 00:18:18,975
…我已经从其他途径找到了消息
...l've had to find information through other means.

266
00:18:19,145 --> 00:18:22,637
我发现你的领养手续 是在大都会的联合慈善机构完成的
I found that your adoption was done through Metropolis United Charities...

267
00:18:22,815 --> 00:18:25,909
…奇怪的地方就在这，他们那时才成立了六个月…
...but this is the strange part. They were in business for six months...

268
00:18:26,085 --> 00:18:28,918
…而且，你是他们唯一的领养案例
...and from what I can tell, yours is the only adoption they handled.

269
00:18:29,088 --> 00:18:30,715
不敢相信你调查这些，克洛伊
I can't believe you did this, Chloe.

270
00:18:32,358 --> 00:18:35,885
你不知道吗？我以为你父母告诉你了
You didn't know? I just assumed that your parents would have told you.

271
00:18:36,062 --> 00:18:38,758
- 我是说，你不感兴趣吗？ - 我为什么要感兴趣？
-I mean, weren't you interested? -Why would I be?

272
00:18:38,932 --> 00:18:41,332
我亲生父母要么过世了要么抛弃了我
My biological parents are either dead or didn't want me.

273
00:18:41,501 --> 00:18:44,868
- 而你正在窥探我的私人生活 - 我只是想彻底搞明白而已
-You're prying into my private life. -I was just trying to be thorough.

274
00:18:45,038 --> 00:18:48,633
不过是一个班级作业 我昨天只花了一小时和拉娜在一起，就这样
This is a class project. I spent an hour yesterday with Lana, that's it.

275
00:18:48,808 --> 00:18:53,006
我需要点小资料就成了 你非把我当成要调查的秘密吗
That's all I needed. I'm not some mystery for you to solve.

276
00:18:54,347 --> 00:18:56,042
克拉克，我…
Clark, I....

277
00:19:01,788 --> 00:19:03,483
说吧，瑞恩斯先生
Talk to me, Mr. Raines.

278
00:19:03,656 --> 00:19:08,184
据门卫说，凯瑟没能赶到你在大都会的公寓
According to the doorman, Kasich never made it to the apartment in Metropolis.

279
00:19:08,361 --> 00:19:11,524
- 罗伊斯呢？ - 他父母在他小时候就过世了
-What about Royce? -His parents died when he was young.

280
00:19:11,698 --> 00:19:15,134
因为车祸，他是独子，继承了所有东西
Car accident. He was an only child, inherited everything.

281
00:19:15,301 --> 00:19:17,667
阿曼达・罗斯曼呢？你跟踪到她了吗？
And Amanda Rothman? Have you tracked her down yet?

282
00:19:17,837 --> 00:19:22,240
她搬走了，没留下地址 你最后一次和她通话是什么时候？
She moved, left no forwarding address. When's the last time you spoke to her?

283
00:19:22,408 --> 00:19:25,707
- 大约三年前 - 我会更深入调查，但需要些时间
-About three years ago. -I'll go wider, but it could take some time.

284
00:19:25,878 --> 00:19:27,743
如果能告诉我发生了什么，或许会有帮助
It'd help if you tell me what's going on.

285
00:19:28,281 --> 00:19:30,306
不，我不能跟你说，你只是安保负责人
No, it wouldn't. You're my head of security.

286
00:19:30,483 --> 00:19:32,644
你找到并警告她可能会有危险
You find her and warn her she could be in danger.

287
00:19:32,819 --> 00:19:34,787
这就是全部你需要知道的
That's all you need to know.

288
00:19:53,373 --> 00:19:57,571
让一下，警察 借过，警察
Make a path. Police. Excuse me, excuse me. Police.

289
00:19:58,111 --> 00:20:01,808
- 你是谁？ - 大都会警察局，警探萨姆・费伦
-Who are you? -Detective Sam Phelan, Metropolis P.D.

290
00:20:01,981 --> 00:20:04,074
你是这破动物园的保安吗？
Are you what passes for security in this zoo?

291
00:20:04,384 --> 00:20:08,252
- 对 - 呆在这，我们得谈谈
-Yeah. -Don't go anywhere. We'll talk.

292
00:20:09,555 --> 00:20:11,887
- 感谢上帝，你来了 - 莱克斯啊，莱克斯啊
-Thank God you're here. -Lex, Lex.

293
00:20:12,058 --> 00:20:14,618
你这回真把事搞大了
You really put your foot in it this time.

294
00:20:14,794 --> 00:20:16,853
告诉我到底发生了什么？
Tell me exactly what happened.

295
00:20:17,864 --> 00:20:20,890
如果你不信任我，我可帮不了你
Hey, if you fall apart on me, I can't help you.

296
00:20:21,067 --> 00:20:23,001
到底发生什么了？
Now what went down?

297
00:20:37,650 --> 00:20:39,311
这是事实？
That's exactly what happened?

298
00:20:40,253 --> 00:20:43,552
好，接下来这样
Good. Here's how it's gonna go.

299
00:20:43,723 --> 00:20:47,784
你从没来过这里，你的名字… …不会出现在任何报纸或者警察笔录里
You were never here. Your name will not appear in any papers or the police report.

300
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:51,794
- 怎么会？ - 这就是你老爸钱的作用
-How? -That's what your daddy's money's for.

301
00:20:52,398 --> 00:20:54,798
这次他要花大价钱了
This one's gonna cost him.

302
00:20:55,168 --> 00:20:59,127
- 阿曼达怎么办？ - 我会安排好每个人的口供
-What about Amanda? -I'll take care of everybody's story...

303
00:20:59,305 --> 00:21:03,071
…但你永远不能再见她 或者再跟她联系，明白吗？
...but you are never to see her or talk to her again. You got it?

304
00:21:03,376 --> 00:21:06,539
给这家伙打电话，他会帮你处理肩伤
Call this guy, he'll take care of your shoulder.

305
00:21:06,946 --> 00:21:09,278
不要去医院
No emergency rooms.

306
00:21:10,450 --> 00:21:12,509
好，出去吧
All right, get out of here.

307
00:21:25,264 --> 00:21:27,994
- 你看到事情经过了？ - 大部分
-Did you see what happened? -Most of it.

308
00:21:28,167 --> 00:21:32,729
高兴点，你因此会得到一大笔钱
Well, smile. Because you're about to come into some serious money.

309
00:21:56,829 --> 00:21:58,160
就没什么要说的吗？
Nothing to say?

310
00:22:02,702 --> 00:22:07,503
- 我以为莱克斯・卢瑟无所不知呢 - 听着，你个变态，杂种
-I thought Lex Luthor had all the answers. -Look, you twisted son of a bitch.

311
00:22:07,673 --> 00:22:10,870
- 我不知道你想要什么 - 我想知道在零点俱乐部发生了什么
-I don't know what you want. -I wanna know what happened at Club Zero.

312
00:22:11,043 --> 00:22:13,011
被掩盖的事实
The cover-up.

313
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:15,814
你知道那个警察吗？
You know the cop?

314
00:22:16,983 --> 00:22:18,951
笔录提到的那个人，费伦？
The one on the report? Phelan?

315
00:22:20,153 --> 00:22:22,246
他死了
He's dead.

316
00:22:22,755 --> 00:22:26,691
似乎你也多少有牵连，太有趣了
It seems that you were somehow involved in that too. I find that very interesting.

317
00:22:28,027 --> 00:22:30,222
你为什么不现在就杀了我？
Why don't you kill me now?

318
00:22:32,031 --> 00:22:34,693
因为看你受折磨更有趣
Because it's more fun to watch you suffer.

319
00:22:35,435 --> 00:22:37,369
看你害怕自己任何时刻都可能会被，砰！
Knowing that at any moment, bang!

320
00:22:41,441 --> 00:22:43,102
告诉我！
Tell me.

321
00:22:44,744 --> 00:22:48,043
到底发生了什么？
What really happened?

322
00:22:49,015 --> 00:22:50,846
莱克斯！
Lex!

323
00:22:56,556 --> 00:22:59,184
莱克斯，你还好吧？
Lex, you all right?

324
00:23:02,929 --> 00:23:04,954
克拉克，你来这干嘛？
Clark, what are you doing here?

325
00:23:05,431 --> 00:23:07,695
你办公室的人告诉我你在这
Your office told me you were here.

326
00:23:09,268 --> 00:23:11,236
我好像听到有其他人在这
I thought I heard someone else.

327
00:23:11,404 --> 00:23:14,134
不，就我一个人
No. I'm all by myself.

328
00:23:15,475 --> 00:23:17,966
嘿，我调查了马克斯・凯瑟
Hey, I looked up Max Kasich.

329
00:23:18,244 --> 00:23:20,212
我知道零点俱乐部发生了什么
I know what happened at Club Zero.

330
00:23:20,379 --> 00:23:25,146
他开枪杀了裘德・罗伊斯 除了你，所有人都被牵扯进来了
That he was shot and killed Jude Royce. Everyone fits into this except for you.

331
00:23:25,885 --> 00:23:28,251
- 怎么了？ - 拜托了，克拉克
-What's going on? -Please, Clark.

332
00:23:28,421 --> 00:23:30,981
为了我们的友谊，拜托你别插手这事
For our friendship, I'm asking you to stay out of this.

333
00:23:31,924 --> 00:23:34,722
一些秘密最好还是不管为妙
Some secrets are better left alone.

334
00:23:41,534 --> 00:23:43,263
克拉克
Clark.

335
00:23:45,538 --> 00:23:49,907
拜托，儿子，牛可不会自己喂自己
Come on, son, the cows aren't gonna feed themselves.

336
00:23:50,176 --> 00:23:52,337
- 你昨晚很晚才睡？ - 我在帮拉娜
-You have a late night? -I was helping Lana.

337
00:23:52,512 --> 00:23:56,710
她不想让断肢事件影响塔龙开业
She's not gonna let the whole body-part incident delay the opening of the Talon.

338
00:23:56,883 --> 00:24:00,512
这就是跟莱克斯・卢瑟这种人打交道的结果
That's what happens when you get into business with somebody like Lex Luthor.

339
00:24:00,686 --> 00:24:03,280
如果不是莱克斯，塔龙就变成停车场了
If it wasn't for Lex, the Talon would be a parking garage.

340
00:24:03,456 --> 00:24:05,447
孩子，真不知他对你的影响会多远
Son, he casts a very, very long shadow.

341
00:24:05,625 --> 00:24:08,594
我只是想保证你们这些孩子不会受伤
I just want to make sure none of you kids get hurt, that's all.

342
00:24:08,761 --> 00:24:12,822
过去的已经过去了，我们最好向前看
The past is in the past. The best we can do is look to the future.

343
00:24:12,999 --> 00:24:14,830
好吧，你说倒我了
All right, you got me.

344
00:24:15,001 --> 00:24:18,129
说到这，克罗伊的论文怎么样了？
Speaking of that, how's Chloe's paper coming along?

345
00:24:18,304 --> 00:24:21,740
- 我想她的采访应该结束了吧 - 不确定
-I assume she's done with her interviews? -I'm not sure.

346
00:24:21,908 --> 00:24:25,241
听我说，克拉克 如果她跟你提及豌豆的事情，我很抱歉
Look, Clark, if she mentions anything to you about the peas, I'm sorry.

347
00:24:25,411 --> 00:24:27,402
这是我当时能想到的第一件事
It's the first thing that came to mind.

348
00:24:27,580 --> 00:24:32,017
如果她跟我提及了大都会慈善联合会呢？
And if she mentions anything to me about the Metropolis United Charities?

349
00:24:34,220 --> 00:24:37,621
我本以为坚持不懈是一种可贵的品质 可她这样真是…
I used to think perseverance was an admirable quality.

350
00:24:38,157 --> 00:24:41,558
自从知道真相，我还没想过领养的事
Since I learned the real truth, I hadn't thought about the adoption.

351
00:24:41,761 --> 00:24:45,561
爸爸，克罗伊告诉我 你们领养我的机构只成立了六个月
Dad, Chloe told me the agency you used was only open six months...

352
00:24:45,731 --> 00:24:48,165
…而我是唯一一个被领养的孩子
...and I was the only kid adopted.

353
00:24:48,434 --> 00:24:50,402
听我说，孩子…
Look, son...

354
00:24:50,970 --> 00:24:54,804
…即使通过正常渠道领养个孩子 过程都很艰辛的
...the process is a really tough one even when you go through normal channels.

355
00:24:54,974 --> 00:24:57,841
领养你，只是更复杂点罢了，就是这样
With you, it was just a little more complicated, that's all.

356
00:24:58,511 --> 00:25:02,447
- 都合法吗？ - 都合法，只是…
-Is everything legal? -Yeah, it's legal, it's just....

357
00:25:02,715 --> 00:25:06,014
当时要办妥这件事 不是我跟你妈能力所及的
Well, it required a higher level of access than your mother or I had.

358
00:25:06,185 --> 00:25:08,119
什么意思？
What does that mean?

359
00:25:10,456 --> 00:25:14,119
我只想跟你说 在地窖里的那个东西和你的出生证明之间…
Let's just say it's a long road between what's sitting in our storm cellar...

360
00:25:14,327 --> 00:25:16,727
…有太复杂的故事
...and what's written on your birth certificate.

361
00:25:19,832 --> 00:25:23,233
- 你听到了吗？ - 听到什么？
-You hear that? -Hear what?

362
00:25:24,403 --> 00:25:27,861
牛群在那边高地，应该能听到动静才对
The whole herd's just over that rise. We ought to be hearing something.

363
00:26:10,683 --> 00:26:12,378
你觉得发生了什么事？
What do you think happened?

364
00:26:12,551 --> 00:26:15,520
为什么卢瑟集团会把废物倒弃这儿？
Why would LuthorCorp dump their stuff here?

365
00:26:24,163 --> 00:26:27,155
我去从别的角度拍些照片
I'm gonna go take from some different angles.

366
00:26:45,351 --> 00:26:49,788
肯特夫妇，我不清楚怎么会这样…
Mr. and Mrs. Kent, I have no idea how this could have happened...

367
00:26:49,955 --> 00:26:54,619
…但我会尽全力找到原因
...but I'll do everything in my power to find out.

368
00:26:55,594 --> 00:26:58,620
我当然也会补偿你的家畜损失
And I'll pay for your livestock, of course.

369
00:26:58,898 --> 00:27:02,061
这就是你解决所有问题的方式吗，莱克斯？
You think that's how you solve everything, don't you, Lex?

370
00:27:02,234 --> 00:27:06,000
撒点钱，就希望问题能消失
You sprinkle a little money on it and hope the problem goes away.

371
00:27:06,706 --> 00:27:10,403
事实上，有些事情可不是那么好办的
Well, obviously, some things are a little more difficult than that.

372
00:27:17,850 --> 00:27:21,411
我还以为我在你父亲心里的形象 不会更差了呢
I didn't think it was possible to fall any further in your father's eyes.

373
00:27:21,587 --> 00:27:23,646
显然，我错了
Obviously, I was wrong.

374
00:27:25,591 --> 00:27:28,219
但我从没放任让这样的事情发生
I'd never intentionally allow something like this to happen.

375
00:27:28,627 --> 00:27:30,788
这跟零点俱乐部有关吗？
Does this have anything to do with Club Zero?

376
00:27:33,966 --> 00:27:36,196
- 我觉得是 - 你得告诉警方…
-I think so. -You need to tell the authorities...

377
00:27:36,368 --> 00:27:39,565
…所有你知道的事情 现在这不只是你个人的事了
...everything you know. This isn't just about you anymore.

378
00:27:46,746 --> 00:27:51,410
卢瑟先生，环保局的人找你谈话，在那边
Mr. Luthor, the C.E.P. guy needs to talk to you. He's over there.

379
00:28:04,296 --> 00:28:06,890
看来你们公司的环境记录要有污点了
Looks like a black mark on your company's environmental record.

380
00:28:07,299 --> 00:28:10,462
- 我要去找治安官 - 跟他说什么？
-I'm gonna walk over and get the sheriff. -And tell him what?

381
00:28:20,446 --> 00:28:22,880
告诉他克拉克・肯特来过电话，谢谢
Just tell him that Clark Kent called. Thank you.

382
00:28:23,048 --> 00:28:24,982
- 打给谁? - 我在找莱克斯
-Who was that? -I'm trying to reach Lex.

383
00:28:25,151 --> 00:28:27,244
他不在公司也不在家…
He's not in the office. He's not at the mansion...

384
00:28:27,419 --> 00:28:29,944
…手机也直接转到语音信箱
...and his cell phone goes straight to voice mail.

385
00:28:30,456 --> 00:28:33,516
- 爸爸在哪？ - 还在监督搬运死牛
-Where's Dad? -Still supervising the removal of the cows.

386
00:28:33,692 --> 00:28:36,593
- 莱克斯说他会赔款的 - 克拉克，这不仅仅是钱的事
-Lex said he'd pay for that. -Clark, this isn't just about money.

387
00:28:36,762 --> 00:28:40,630
谁也不知道这会对我们和邻居的健康 造成什么样的威胁
We don't know what kind of health threat this poses to us or to our neighbors.

388
00:28:41,834 --> 00:28:43,426
我想这不是莱克斯的错
I don't think this is Lex's fault.

389
00:28:43,602 --> 00:28:47,265
我想有人在陷害他，因为夜店的事
I think someone is trying to set him up because of what happened at the nightclub.

390
00:28:47,439 --> 00:28:48,963
看
Look.

391
00:28:49,900 --> 00:28:51,000
零点俱乐部死亡事件

392
00:28:51,610 --> 00:28:54,704
- 事情还不明朗之前，我不想… - 莱克斯一直是个很好的朋友
-Until this is cleared up, I don't-- -Lex has always been a good friend.

393
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:56,848
我知道，我也一直维护他…
I know. I'm usually the one who defends him...

394
00:28:57,016 --> 00:29:00,144
…但他过去的名声确实不好
...but there are some things in his past that are a little shady.

395
00:29:00,686 --> 00:29:02,551
我以为咱们家不以过去评价人呢
In this family we don't look at the past.

396
00:29:02,721 --> 00:29:06,384
克拉克，我在大都会长大 我了解卢瑟家族
Clark, I grew up in Metropolis, I know the Luthor world.

397
00:29:06,559 --> 00:29:09,585
看上去诱惑又有趣，但他们的孩子都太早熟…
It looks glamorous and fun, but the kids grow up too fast...

398
00:29:09,762 --> 00:29:11,286
…很容易陷入麻烦
...and they can get into trouble.

399
00:29:11,630 --> 00:29:14,190
莱克斯的事情已经开始影响你了
Whatever's happening to Lex is starting to affect you.

400
00:29:14,366 --> 00:29:18,666
盒子里的断肢和中毒的奶牛？ 这些都不正常
Body parts in boxes and poisoned cows? This isn't normal.

401
00:29:19,038 --> 00:29:21,336
你想让我怎么做？跟他断绝关系？
What do you want me to do? Cut him out of my life?

402
00:29:21,507 --> 00:29:25,136
不，我希望你暂时冷下这段友情 直到我们清楚到底发生了什么
No, I want you to cool it off for a while until we know what really happened.

403
00:29:25,811 --> 00:29:30,111
我和你爸爸不想你被他的问题牵连
Your father and I just don't want to see you pulled into his problems.

404
00:29:40,192 --> 00:29:42,422
我能跟你谈谈吗？
Can I talk to you for a second?

405
00:29:46,498 --> 00:29:47,988
你好吗？
How you doing?

406
00:29:48,167 --> 00:29:52,126
- 那要看你要不要录音了 - 好吧，我道歉
-That depends if it's on the record or not. -Okay, I deserve that.

407
00:29:52,304 --> 00:29:56,536
我并没想拿领养机构的事来套你的话
Look, I didn't mean to ambush you with the whole adoption agency thing.

408
00:29:56,876 --> 00:29:59,504
你看到有故事，就去调查
Hey, you saw a story and you went right for it.

409
00:29:59,678 --> 00:30:01,669
- 记者就这么做的 - 你是对的
-That's what journalists do. -You're right.

410
00:30:01,847 --> 00:30:03,838
我没想到这会伤害到你
I didn't think about how it would hurt you.

411
00:30:04,016 --> 00:30:08,077
你知道，虽然记者的本性有些反叛
And, you know, as much as journalistic instinct rebels...

412
00:30:08,254 --> 00:30:10,449
…但我不想因为一个课题失去朋友
...l'd rather have a friend than a subject...

413
00:30:10,623 --> 00:30:13,319
…所以我不再调查了
...so I'm dropping the whole thing.

414
00:30:15,728 --> 00:30:17,457
谢谢
Thank you.

415
00:30:18,664 --> 00:30:20,791
我能问个问题吗？
Can I ask you a question?

416
00:30:21,367 --> 00:30:23,494
绝对没有录音
Totally off the record.

417
00:30:25,638 --> 00:30:28,266
你想知道自己的亲生父母吗？
Do you ever wonder about your biological parents?

418
00:30:29,975 --> 00:30:32,068
生命里的每一天都在想
Every day of my life.

419
00:30:39,385 --> 00:30:42,149
看来我不是唯一做调查的人
Looks like I'm not the only one doing some digging.

420
00:30:42,321 --> 00:30:44,619
- 零点俱乐部怎么了？ - 跟莱克斯的过去有关
-What's Club Zero? -Part of Lex's past...

421
00:30:44,790 --> 00:30:47,054
…他让我不要管
...he asked me to stay out of.

422
00:30:48,994 --> 00:30:52,430
我刚好给你父母带了些照片来
By the way, I brought by some pictures for your parents.

423
00:30:52,598 --> 00:30:55,658
申请保险赔偿的时候可能用的上
I figured they could use it for insurance purposes and stuff.

424
00:30:55,834 --> 00:30:58,098
我得走了
I'll see you later. I gotta go.

425
00:30:58,270 --> 00:30:59,862
克罗伊…
Chloe...

426
00:31:02,041 --> 00:31:03,906
…是同一个人
...it's the same guy.

427
00:31:08,280 --> 00:31:10,339
- 可是他不是已经… - 死了
-Wait, but he's-- -Dead.

428
00:31:23,262 --> 00:31:24,991
救命!
Help!

429
00:31:25,798 --> 00:31:27,993
有人吗？
Somebody!

430
00:31:28,634 --> 00:31:30,829
救命！
Help!

431
00:31:31,603 --> 00:31:33,730
救命！
Help!

432
00:31:38,610 --> 00:31:40,134
有人吗？
Somebody!

433
00:31:40,879 --> 00:31:43,541
没有莱克斯的回话 早上到现在都没人联系得上他
No word from Lex. No one's spoken to him since this morning.

434
00:31:43,716 --> 00:31:47,516
我调出了这个所谓的死人的驾照 是用约翰・史密斯这个名字登记的，是原件
I pulled our alleged dead guy's license. It's registered to a John Smith. Original.

435
00:31:47,686 --> 00:31:50,450
他在大都会有个地址 但不是在环保局工作的
He has an address in Metropolis and does not work for the C.E.P.

436
00:31:50,622 --> 00:31:52,886
- 你怎么做到的？ - 我黑进了车辆管理局的数据库
-How'd you do that? -I hacked into the DMV database.

437
00:31:53,058 --> 00:31:55,618
- 有时候坚持不懈依然是个优点吧 - 打电话给大都会警察局
-Sometimes persistence is a good thing. -Call Metropolis P.D.

438
00:31:55,794 --> 00:31:58,126
- 让他们去那个地址 - 发生了什么？
-Have them go to that address. -What's going on?

439
00:31:58,297 --> 00:32:00,162
我想莱克斯有大麻烦了
I think Lex is in serious trouble.

440
00:32:08,807 --> 00:32:10,798
准备要说了吗？
You ready to talk?

441
00:32:12,544 --> 00:32:15,877
你终于到了三年前就应该在的地方
You're finally where you should have been three years ago.

442
00:32:17,583 --> 00:32:19,778
暴露在聚光灯下
Exposed in the spotlight.

443
00:32:19,952 --> 00:32:22,512
你想要我怎么样？
What do you want from me?

444
00:32:23,155 --> 00:32:25,851
说出零点俱乐部里的真相
The truth about Club Zero.

445
00:32:26,851 --> 00:32:27,851
大都会警局车

446
00:32:53,585 --> 00:32:55,177
凯瑟
Kasich.

447
00:32:55,354 --> 00:32:58,255
打扰了，请问里面还有别人吗？
Excuse me, did you find anyone else in there?

448
00:33:02,828 --> 00:33:06,229
- 你知道零点俱乐部在哪吗？ - 孩子，你问晚了六个月了
-Do you know where I can find Club Zero? -You're six months too late, kid.

449
00:33:06,632 --> 00:33:08,463
- 什么意思？ - 已经关门了
-What do you mean? -Well, it closed down.

450
00:33:08,634 --> 00:33:10,693
就是第78道和主干道路口的一间旧仓库
It was an old warehouse on 78th and Main.

451
00:33:14,373 --> 00:33:18,104
骗子！那只是报道上说的，但不是真相
Liar! That's what it said in the papers, but that's not what really happened.

452
00:33:18,277 --> 00:33:21,610
- 事实就是这样，看警察笔录去吧！ - 我知道你掩盖得很全面
-It's the truth. Read the police reports! -I know you covered it up.

453
00:33:21,780 --> 00:33:24,874
虽然我不知道你怎么做到的 但你要为此付出代价
I don't know how you did it, but you're gonna pay.

454
00:33:25,050 --> 00:33:26,483
你是谁？
Who are you?

455
00:33:27,619 --> 00:33:29,610
不记得了吗？
Don't you remember?

456
00:33:32,157 --> 00:33:33,590
你杀了我
You killed me.

457
00:33:41,767 --> 00:33:44,292
这次你爸也救不了你，莱克斯
Daddy can't save you this time, Lex.

458
00:34:09,928 --> 00:34:11,691
游戏结束了，莱克斯
No more games, Lex.

459
00:34:12,998 --> 00:34:15,262
真相大白的时间到了
It's time for the truth.

460
00:34:27,813 --> 00:34:30,805
我认得你，你是塔龙的建筑承保人
I know you. You're the contractor from the Talon.

461
00:34:30,983 --> 00:34:33,213
那是我白天的工作
That's my day job.

462
00:34:36,855 --> 00:34:38,584
你是谁？
Who are you?

463
00:34:39,424 --> 00:34:41,289
阿曼达从没和你谈过她的家人吗？
Amanda never talked about her family?

464
00:34:42,628 --> 00:34:45,825
她说过她有个哥哥，在中央城
She said she had a brother in Central City.

465
00:34:46,098 --> 00:34:48,931
他在监狱里 阿曼达是唯一和他联系的人
He was in prison. She was the only person who kept in touch.

466
00:34:49,101 --> 00:34:50,864
在监狱里时，我就视她为我的生命
She was my lifeline when I was inside.

467
00:34:51,036 --> 00:34:53,300
可惜我没有个能把我从监狱里弄出来的富老爸
I never had a rich daddy to keep me out of jail.

468
00:34:53,772 --> 00:34:56,969
- 我不明白，你想要什么？ - 我要什么？我要什么？
-I don't understand. What do you want? -What do I want? What do I want?

469
00:34:57,142 --> 00:35:00,737
我要帮我妹妹复仇
I want vengeance for my sister.

470
00:35:03,048 --> 00:35:05,573
什么意思？阿曼达在哪？
What do you mean? Where's Amanda?

471
00:35:05,751 --> 00:35:07,878
她死了，莱克斯
She's dead, Lex.

472
00:35:08,053 --> 00:35:10,078
她一年前自杀了
She committed suicide a year ago.

473
00:35:13,091 --> 00:35:16,322
- 我没听说 - 那是因为你对她不管不顾
-I never knew. -That's because you cut her out of your life.

474
00:35:17,162 --> 00:35:21,326
零点俱乐部那事之后，她完全变了 裘德的死毁了她
She was never the same after Club Zero. Jude's death devastated her.

475
00:35:21,500 --> 00:35:25,527
他是她生命中挚爱，你夺走了他
He was the love of her life. You took all that away.

476
00:35:26,305 --> 00:35:28,330
她失去了活下去的希望
She had nothing to live for.

477
00:35:31,276 --> 00:35:33,073
那是谁？
Who's that?

478
00:35:34,146 --> 00:35:36,273
意外的好运
Lucky break.

479
00:35:36,715 --> 00:35:40,515
阿曼达葬礼后几星期 我去布鲁德海文市的一家小餐馆
Couple weeks after Amanda's funeral, I walk into a greasy spoon in Bludhaven...

480
00:35:40,686 --> 00:35:44,520
在那碰到他，我都不敢相信 一个做汉堡的快餐厨师
...and there he is. I couldn't believe it. Short-order cook flipping burgers.

481
00:35:44,690 --> 00:35:49,593
你听过“现实中会有另一个自己”的说法吗？ 连我都得仔细看看
You know how they say everyone in life has a double? I had to look twice.

482
00:35:50,295 --> 00:35:54,288
我在想，如果他能骗到我，也能骗到你
I figure if he can fool me, he can fool you.

483
00:35:56,935 --> 00:35:58,368
他为什么要这么做？
Why'd he do it?

484
00:35:59,471 --> 00:36:02,804
他在保释中，需要钱，我就有了这个想法
He was on parole, needed the money, and that's when I got the idea.

485
00:36:02,975 --> 00:36:07,105
你毁了我妹妹曼蒂的生活 我也要毁了你的
You ruined Mandy's life, I'd ruin yours.

486
00:36:07,779 --> 00:36:10,612
曼蒂终于能得到她应得的公正了
Mandy's finally gonna get the justice she deserves.

487
00:36:11,483 --> 00:36:13,508
你说对了，没错
You were right.

488
00:36:14,453 --> 00:36:19,618
报纸，警方笔录，和我对费伦所说的
You were right. The newspapers, the police reports, what I told Phelan.

489
00:36:19,958 --> 00:36:23,792
全是假的，你想要真相？我告诉你
They were all lies. You want the truth? I'll give it to you.

490
00:36:58,697 --> 00:37:02,758
- 不，你又在扭曲事实！ - 这就是真正发生的事！
-No, no, no. You're twisting it again! -That's what happened!

491
00:37:02,934 --> 00:37:05,061
这就是事实，阿曼达扣动了扳机
That's what happened. Amanda pulled the trigger.

492
00:37:05,237 --> 00:37:07,603
她杀了裘德 我隐瞒这一切都是为了保护她
She shot Jude. I was just trying to protect her.

493
00:37:07,773 --> 00:37:09,035
我受够你了，莱克斯！
I'm through with you, Lex!

494
00:37:11,310 --> 00:37:13,107
杀了我，阿曼达也不会回来了
Killing me won't bring Amanda back.

495
00:37:13,312 --> 00:37:16,577
- 这一切都改变不了发生过的事 - 我不管
-None of this can change what happened. -I don't care.

496
00:37:16,748 --> 00:37:18,875
今晚之后，你不会再伤害任何人了
After tonight, you'll never hurt anyone else.

497
00:37:19,184 --> 00:37:21,675
你逃不了过去的，莱克斯
You can't escape your past, Lex.

498
00:37:40,739 --> 00:37:42,229
莱克斯！
Lex!

499
00:37:42,407 --> 00:37:44,466
趴下！楼上有人有枪
Get down! There's a man with a gun up there.

500
00:37:44,643 --> 00:37:47,134
哪里？你是说他？
Where? You mean that guy?

501
00:37:47,312 --> 00:37:50,975
- 发生了什么？ - 我不知道
-What happened? -I have no idea.

502
00:37:51,149 --> 00:37:53,413
你怎么找到我的？
How'd you find me here?

503
00:37:53,585 --> 00:37:55,348
靠我朋友的一点帮助
With a little help from my friends.

504
00:38:24,616 --> 00:38:28,814
- 你觉得怎么样？ - 我很惊讶
-So, what do you think? -I'm definitely surprised.

505
00:38:28,987 --> 00:38:30,682
我也是
Me too.

506
00:38:31,056 --> 00:38:32,853
克罗伊在哪？
Where's Chloe?

507
00:38:33,291 --> 00:38:36,454
她说要像明星一样，晚到一点
She said she wanted to be fashionably late.

508
00:38:39,431 --> 00:38:40,955
这个送给你
I got this for you.

509
00:38:42,100 --> 00:38:44,091
别担心，不是断肢
Don't worry, it's not a body part.

510
00:38:45,904 --> 00:38:48,236
在阁楼上找到的，是我爷爷的
It was in the attic. It was my grandfather's.

511
00:38:48,407 --> 00:38:51,137
塔龙当年刚开张时照的
It was taken just after the Talon opened.

512
00:38:51,510 --> 00:38:56,447
- 你可以把它挂在柜台上 - 克拉克，太惊喜了，谢谢
-Figured you could hang it above the counter. -Clark, it's amazing. Thank you.

513
00:38:57,416 --> 00:38:59,145
不用谢
You're welcome.

514
00:39:00,385 --> 00:39:02,785
我要回去做事了
I better get back to work.

515
00:39:03,321 --> 00:39:05,255
感觉怎么样？
How does it feel?

516
00:39:05,524 --> 00:39:10,291
- 有点怕，不要告诉别人 - 我会为你保守秘密的
-Terrifying. Don't tell anybody. -Your secret's safe with me.

517
00:39:21,606 --> 00:39:23,938
我感觉你在躲我，克拉克
I get the feeling you're avoiding me, Clark.

518
00:39:24,976 --> 00:39:27,911
我发现自己对你很不了解
I just realized there's a lot I don't know about you.

519
00:39:28,079 --> 00:39:30,479
怕我不光彩的过去会影响你？
You think my dark past is gonna rub off on you?

520
00:39:33,652 --> 00:39:35,882
我撒谎说自己开的枪 是为了保护阿曼达
I was trying to protect Amanda.

521
00:39:36,054 --> 00:39:37,885
我爸爸根本不会去帮她…
My father wouldn't raise a finger to help her...

522
00:39:38,056 --> 00:39:40,115
…但我知道他肯定会尽量保护他独子的
...but I knew he'd do anything to save his only son.

523
00:39:40,559 --> 00:39:43,687
所以你代人受罪，才掩盖了真相？
So you took the fall and everything was covered up?

524
00:39:44,129 --> 00:39:47,189
这是真正发生的事吗？这是真相吗？
Is that really what happened? Is it the truth?

525
00:39:48,900 --> 00:39:52,336
真相就是，我会尽我所能去保护我的朋友
The truth is, I'd do anything to protect my friends.

526
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:56,336
大都会联合慈善机构


